TSX and AIM-listed Thor Explorations has released a positive operational and financial review for its mineral properties located in Nigeria, Senegal and Burkina Faso for the three months to 31 March 2022. Operational highlights of the period Watch: One on one with Segun Lawson Financial highlights of the period Outlook Segun Lawson, president and CEO, stated, “The company’s performance in Q1 2022 provides a solid foundation for the rest of the year. Segilola is now running efficiently and the company continues to be on track to achieve its guidance of 80 000 to 100 000 ounces of gold this year within our AISC guidance of $850-$950 per ounce. “We are also proud of our ESG efforts in and around the local communities. We are particularly proud to share our inaugural sustainability report, which will be published later in the year.”